  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Brown the oxtail on all sides in batches, about 5 minutes per batch.",
    "Remove the browned oxtail from the pot and set aside.",
    "Add the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil to the pot, then saut\u00049 the onion, carrot, and celery until tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, allspice, and bay leaves to the pot and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the browned oxtail, apple cider vinegar, beef broth, and sugar to the pot, cover, and transfer to the oven.",
    "Bake for 2 1/2 hours or until the meat is tender.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and stir in the flour to thicken the sauce.",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with fresh herbs if desired."
